Me at 1 year old- it’s weird being the same age as old people 🤪

THIS PAINTING IS A GREAT EXAMPLE OF MY LATEST WORK - for me it’s really next level - I keep learning - experimenting and trying to express these complicated ideas and emotions - and BTW GRATTITUDE IS STILL THE KEY TO MY LITTLE LIFE - even when I’m annoyed or upset I find that within me -I’m still so grateful - IM STILL HERE ! Rock on !

Within me - there is an Invincible Summer .. and that makes me happy! Yep, I’m riffing on Camus. Who knew! I love this letter Camus wrote to his friend - I always felt this way, but couldn’t describe it. This passage articulated it all so beautifully - and that also makes me happy - potent stuff

IF WE ARE MATURE WE CAN LEARN AND GROW FROM OUR BROTHERS WE CALL THE OPPOSITION -  I found this quote from the great MLK many years ago - it allways stuck with me - I even painted it a few times - it’s a powerful message

If you haven’t visited our Hebru Brantley solo show “BOUND” in the Wynwood Walls - THE TIME IS NOW ! This exhibition will be open to the public for another month - see you soon we are all here daily. DM me if you would like to collect an original Hebru
@wynwoodwallsofficial @hebrubrantley @goldmanglobalarts
New Year- New Work
Good Morning! Everyday as I open up this fantastically degraded door, I wonder what will transpire in that wacky wonderful room - and basically everyday my mind gets blown
Sometimes you gotta just let go - going for it

One day I just spontaneously grabbed a container of black paint and literally just DRIPPED this CAPE BUFFALO (no water buff in east Africa) Having low to no expectations - I completed it like 10 minutes. It was an experiment and a miracle the way it turned out. I eventually sold it to a “brilliant collector” 🤓 He recently asked me for an American Buffalo. I’m pretty stoked to just go for it - but honestly, I have NO IDEA how to do it or IF I EVEN CAN DO IT !! It’s such an unforgiving way to paint - you MUST embrace every “mistake” everything matters - I do like traveling into totally unknown jungles - les go !

Over the past year I have been creating a few paintings based on Bored Apes and Mutant apes - MAN OF STEEL was one of my favorites and begs the question would you rather own the painting with many large apes OR the NFT ? The journey continues - I used my own Mutant Ape for MUNKEY BUSINESS - if you own an ape why not own the painting too?

GOOD GOOD ! Being installed at @lab18golf - wow what an incredible and fun project - I’ll share more as we complete the installation - 16 pieces IN TOTAL throughout their NEXT LEVEL FACILITY. GOOD GOOD is the centerpiece and is hung near the putting area - if you are in Long Island and are into golf - you gotta check it out - Thank you Josh !
I saw this on the news stands this week IN EVERY STAND - such great news! No wonder it’s on the cover of a magazine ! Spread the news dude
FEAR LESS - two words - btw thats Marlon Brando in the cowboy hat
I haven’t done C’EST LA VIE in a while - here it is !
This funny segment with Harry Smith aired 5 years ago Sunday - wow wow wow - TIME JUST FLIES - Art was 2 !! Wow
I really enjoy having this MONSTER PIECE right next to my desk - and I allways loved the original movie 🍿

Welcome to SUPERBOWL SUNDAY !! I remember the Chiefs vs Niners Super Bowl in Miami at Hard Rock Stadium like it was yesterday - that was the last big public event before Covid. Tristan Eaton’s art work for the ticket and program was astounding and then he went 3D and created this huge sculpture which remains on view at Hard Rock Stadium along with his sik mural ! @tristaneaton @goldmanglobalarts
Happy Feb 14th - this is our one and only LIFE - let’s love it - and enjoy our LOVE LIFE !
THIS IS A MURAL BY THE ASTOUNDING ARTIST LEON KEER - his solo exhibition coming soon in the GGA GALLERY IN THE WYNWOOD WALLS - stay tuned -   @leonkeer
I’m just soo busy today
NEW BLAZING SKULLS!
You talkin to me? Surfs up dude

This is one of my favorite commissions from a treasured client -  it’s now hanging in their winter wonderland - he came up with the words and the theme was the beauty and joy of winter and the magic of snow ❄️
Two of my favorite boards - surfs up dude - but these are NOT for surfing 🏄‍♀️ - I always liked Oscar Wilde’s definition of art : ALL THINGS USELESS 🥸
Can you see this !?

Well I did the official taste test of the “HARAJUKU” Burger- and WOW - that was a full on super glorious food experience - BEST BURGER EVER PERIOD !! Insane ! Next level !! How do YOU get one!? Order now at www.shibuyasando.com and on Instagram @shibuya.sando - also available on DoorDash and Caviar
NEW WORK FROM ‘NEW MASTERS’ Exhibition - currently on view at the BANK O’ THE FUTURE in Wynwood - swipe to see a few more. These are all real oil paintings with my unique embellishments !

The GAME CHANGER mobile and medical research lab is still on the move. I am THRILLED to announce that Vehicle #3 is now on the road! It’s been an unbelievable journey and an incredibly successful project across the board. For 5 years now, these amazing vehicles roll into neighborhoods and communities providing diagnostic tests for early detection and disease prevention. Delivering these tests to the neighborhood has in fact been a GAME CHANGER. It’s a genuine success story that is now being replicated in many other states. Thank you to Dr. Stephen Nimer, Jayne Sylvester Malfitano, Dr. Erin Kobetzk and the incredible team at the UM Sylvester Cancer Center @erinkobetzk @sylvestercancer

GIANT SIZED GIANT POLAROID - I found this old Marlboro pack in the street in NYC and from that small piece of street trash eventually made an entire show - one man’s trash … is another man’s treasure. My favorite practice of art making is turning trash into TREASURE that’s for sure
NEXT LEVEL AMERICAN FLAG - a breakthrough for me and a real breakthrough thought - maybe everything is going to be amazing - wow - imagine that !!  I’m ready for it ! I’m all in everyday
SPOTTED- “LONELY NO MORE”- It is a little thrill to see your art displayed by others - I also love a ton of fat white paint liberally applied - dripping off the sides like melted ice cream

Which animals do you see in this tree trunk - giraffe - large antelope lying down looking back at you - horse - zebra - BONGO! - the truth is there is magic, real magic, everywhere we look - in stillness magic appears - what a day what a journey

Oh and this happened yesterday… I was sitting in my car in my driveway for over an hour on a long call - I got out and went to bed and a few hours later I was awakened by a big crash - Well… this huge 75 year old tree in my front yard blew over, obliterated my concrete fence, and totaled my FORD! 

Upon seeing that scene I was soooo grateful that no one was hurt - it could have happened any day - any night - any hour - and after 75 majestic years it missed me by a few hours and I was sitting there for over an hour ! I never thought my new car would get totaled and I’d be grateful - I AM - I STILL AM - ahh this life

This is but one incredible “painting“ by the incomparable LEON KEER - I feel and look rather small next to his work. This is a show you have to experience in person - hope to see you Thursday in the Wynwood Walls 4-9pm for the unveiling  and opening - prepare to go NEXT LEVEL !
Thursday 4-9 PM - Leon Keer solo show “SEEING THINGS” Be there or be square! @leonkeer @ggagalleryofficial

David, Beth, Peter and John Tunney - aka the Tunney’s - so good to be with my brothers and sister- I know I know THATS A LOT OF TUNNEYS IN ONE ROOM - blessed with these loving siblings- thanks for coming !! I loved it all!

Just completed this piece - I’m grateful and appreciative of all the gifts the UNITED STATES has to offer - of course these are TESTING TIMES here and around the world - the arc of happiness is often really long - but I’m hopeful and so stoked for the rest of this day !! BRAVE NEW WORLD indeed - find your courage and hope and positivity - it’s true, THE FUTURE AINT WHAT IT USED TO BE — it’s actually better than you ever imagined !! Les GO !

TOTAL JOY EXISTS .. could anything really be better than this ? Just a joyous dream - INDELIBLE MOMENTS IN TIME -  may be the best time I’ve ever had !! And It’s also my cardio for the day - do that 200 times and you really feel it 🤪 THANK YOU GOD - beyond grattitide dude

I love you! If you were at our wedding please reply with your favorite memory / moment

DUDE … really... seriously? I just stumbled upon this piece I made for the “REDACTED “ exhibition years ago - I really loved that show and loved creating the pieces, but honestly didn’t think it would be very well received - and then it sold out - I’m almost always wrong

“Heaven is under our feet as well as over our heads “ the quote is Henry David Thoreau - and in case you didn’t know ..it’s lambing season in Northern Ireland! 10 new puppies and 20 baby lambs at the farm-tools - tractors - mud - quad bikes- 10 PUPPIES! The kids are in heaven - just dreamy
MY DAILY MISSION - FINDING CLAM IN THE CHAOS 🤪

OWN THE DAY ! I’m still processing and expressing this Emerson quote - I find it pops up all day - especially keeping out the FRET AND ANXIETY - potent stuff. Here it is in full:
“Write it on your heart that every day is the best day in the year. He is rich who owns the day, and no one owns the day who allows it to be invaded with fret and anxiety. Finish every day and be done with it. You have done what you could. Some blunders and absurdities, no doubt crept in. Forget them as soon as you can, tomorrow is a new day; begin it well and serenely, with too high a spirit to be cumbered with your old nonsense. This new day is too dear, with its hopes and invitations, to waste a moment on the yesterdays.” - Ralph Waldo Emerson
Lesson Learned.

My thoughts and prayers are with his family and friends. HARRY NEVER WAVERED AND DEEPLY AFFECTED THE WORLD - he was THE example of what one person can achieve - THANK YOU HARRY for being an indelible force in our lives - you will be missed but never forgotten

THE TIME IS ALLWAYS NOW TO MEET THE MOMENT YOU ARE IN
NOWWHERE

Life is indeed a journey - a rocky road to say the least, but it is our one and only life and no one gets out alive. A GOOD LIFE is my hope for everyone - nobody said it was easy. Today, I’m just feeling grateful to be here - struggling, toiling, lots of failures, occasionally succeeding - but I’m still here and still going and going and going!

This time of year I can’t help but think of where I was 48 years ago - I was hit by a car on May 23, 1975 while coming down a long hill at top speed on my ten speed bike. That moment changed everything and deeply affected not only me but my sweet parents and wonderful brothers and sisters , friends - classmates etc - life happens fast. I got that clock - radio for my birthday on Sept 1 , 1975 and was still on crutches throughout 1976 and performed many magic shows even while in a body cast. I am so grateful to still be here - still performing magic daily and humbly reminded - you just never know what comes next and I’m ok with that - I AM HERE NOW and so are you - so let’s go !!
HERE NOW
JUST GRATEFUL BEYOND WORDS - miracles DO happen

ITS ALL DREAM TIME - every day is so precious, fragile, filled with hope and invitation. Most of the TIME I feel like I’m living in a dream - just here floating along in this wild vast ocean of life - but alas even living in THE DREAM is really hard sometimes. Oh well NOBODY SAID IT WAS EASY. Enjoy another spectacular SUN ☀️DAY

Last year, Jesse proposed to Blake in my Tribeca gallery and presented her with a special personalized “TODAY IS THE DAY” piece to memorialize the moment. She said YES and they were married last weekend in NYC and projected their message at the wedding venue - special stuff! Sincere congratulations to you and your families - with love and grattitude - Pt

SO WHAT! This was an ORIGINAL GIANT POLAROID TAKEN MANY YEARS AGO. It was pulled out of a drawer and now has a new life - what’s old is new …again. A discarded object magically becomes a one-of-a-kind treasure

“In the midst of hate, I found there was within me, an invincible love. In the midst of tears, I found there was within me, an invincible smile. In the midst of chaos, I found there was within me, an invincible calm. I realized, through it all, that in the midst of winter, I found there was within me, an invincible summer. And that makes me happy. For it says that no matter how hard the world pushes against me, within me, there’s something stronger- something better, pushing right back.” - Albert Camus
14 years later- The Wynwood Walls is still my happy place. See you soon!

The astounding art making process of @dankitchener - this is Dan just using freehand spray paint !! Swipe to see the finished piece LONDON LIGHTS. Thank you DANK for your supreme efforts and generosity of spirit - you are the real deal sir

I remember this magic moment - giving arthur a bath in a salad bowl at @noahtepperberg and @melissawoodtepperberg house in the Hamptons when he was 8 WEEKS OLD -  Arthur just turned 8 YEARS OLD - I VIVIDLY remember looking into his eyes in that bowl - he was a deep thinker even then - time does fly - Happy 8th Birthday Art - it’s been an unbelievably life enhancing 8 years knowing you - loving you and learning life lessons from you ! @amytunney

NEW MASTERS- currently on view in Wynwood. This collection of ten original oil paintings embellished with contemporary messages and objects installed at The Bank O the Future was a vision of mine for 30 years ! Cruising around in here tonight I saw it all with new eyes - it’s really unbelievable that I’ve ended up HERE in this WILLY WONKA MEETS PT BARNUM FUNNY WORLD - ITS A MAD MAD MAD MAD WORLD - grateful !

You never know how a collector is going to install their piece. Most collectors have their own VISION of how, where, and why they hang a piece of art - this installation by @pparthenisjr is one of the coolest placements ever ! Wow wow wow - btw this piece is made from custom made matchbooks which also serve as my official business card - this photo made my day thank you guys !!
But they never told you how hard it could be! Stay strong

Yep I get into it !! Basically transferring my human energy and all my emotions into every painting - all pulsing off my little nervous system.
I try to leave it all in the ring on every painting I create - its a real cathartic process. I usually get going during night sessions in the studio 
I created this diptych for @lab18golf in Roslyn. If you’re into golf and you’re in Long Island- you’ve got to check it out. Swipe to see the installation

A very thoughtful collector and a fantastic installation - if you see that message everyday when you wake up it WILL GET IN YOUR HEAD! I loved this project and am blown away to see how it lives in a home - Thank you @idhands - it’s been an honor
It’s really such a thrill to surprisingly see one of my paintings living in someone’s home - especially when it looks Sooo tasty - and with a cool pool table🤩😎!
“The only things that we may take are the things we give away. If we have helped others, we may take that with us.”
Just another day at the office - we all made it to yet another Friday ! And that makes me smile. SAVOR EVERY HOUR !
WE ARE ALL JUST HUMAN - AFTER ALL,  DO YOU KNOW ANYONE WHO HAS NEVER STUMBLED ? Rock on 🤘!

After I “declared”  myself an Artist in late 1987- I painted and collaged my actual TV- I left one small rectangle of the screen unpainted and I watched TV like this for a solid 10 years.. who would ever believe the journey that ensued - truth is definitely stranger than fiction !! I allways considered this my first piece of Art -time flies !!
Early daze in the Wynwood walls - I just had one plastic folding table with a tarp thrown over it - I loved it then and I love it more now 14 years later -

Sept 11, 2001 - 22 short years ago - it was a potent and indelible day and time in my life - and a seminal day for us all - I’m in lower Manhattan today - reflecting - still processing the world that has unfolded since then - my heart goes out to so so many who lost loved ones that day - we are all forever changed - when I open that old coffee can a flood of memories pour out - god bless us all

Tribeca current studio installation - I tweaked this whole place today - once in a while I go through and literally touch every single object and adjust and move things around -  this little area is just the way I like it -🤪 and every little object has an origination story - it’s ridiculous and overwhelming and I love it - Thank you sincerely for everyone that came by tonight

All of these beautiful students attend The Acadamie for Peace and Justice which was created from the ground up over the last ten years on a patch of parched land in Haiti by all the amazing and generous supporters of Artists for Peace and Justice (APJ). @artistsforpeace 

Today over 3,000 students attend APJ free public high school just outside of Port Au Prince - we began this journey 15 short years ago and this year at TIFF. @natashankpr hosted the sold out APJ Gala a few days ago

It was an astounding and nourishing evening filled with authentic music, sounds and testimonials from our graduates we have educated over 25,000 students and have thousands of high school graduates

A huge thank you to the spectacular village that has kept the flame alive during incredibly challenging times IMPOSSIBLE IS OFTEN POSSIBLE !!

Repost @natashankpr :
“Life is partly what we make it, and partly what it is made by the friends we choose.” 

Before we dive into this cover, I want to take some time to reflect on the significance of designing your life alongside like-minded people. To me, relationships hold immeasurable value, not for personal gain, but for the potential that emerges when two or more souls align. 💫

For over two decades, I’ve been fortunate to call @petertunney my friend. Together, we’ve created moments of mischief 😅 and moments of great impact. Our collaborative work spans from initiatives like @artistsforpeace and our passion for creating change in #Haiti to our work with #NatashatheResidences. 

I have so much of his meaningful artwork throughout my spaces. From the moment you step into my home, you’re met with ‘Gratitude’. When you enter my office, you’ll find the words ‘Treasured Time.’ Even the @rickowensonline dress I’m wearing on the cover has Peter’s touch, with the word ‘LIBERTY’ on its side - these words serve as a reminder of our shared values. 🤗

I am deeply honored to grace the September cover of @livingluxemagazine alongside my friend and kindred spirit, @petertunney. Our journey has been a remarkable one, and it’s a testament to what happens when like-minded individuals unite. 🙌🏼

To read more about our friendship dynamic and amazing journey, grab your copy of the September issue of @livingluxemagazine available at a newsstand near you.”

I moved into my cinder block one story warehouse in the Wynwood Walls 14 years ago - who could’ve possibly seen what was going to happen - well the answer is Tony Goldman , he saw it all - and his beautiful vision for this thriving community came true. I fondly remember being the only one here with a folding table as my desk -  TEMPUS FUGIT - and so grateful for the incredible journey I’ve been on with all of you and with the entire Goldman Family - it’s been an epic,  legendary , storied run - we now begin 2024 and continue the DREAM TIME  - the Wynwood Walls and the entire campus is officially mind blowing - see you soon
